thread.title: Halesowen Town: Misery as Yeltz are hit for six
thread.title_full: Halesowen Town: Misery as Yeltz are hit for six

title: Halesowen Town: Misery as Yeltz are hit for six
text:
Tweet 
The red card occurred on only eight minutes when Jay Denny walked for apparently stamping on Callum Woodward, with Danny Bragoli and Barwell’s Nigel Julien also booked for their part in the incident. 
Four minutes later, former Yeltz hero Iyseden Christie lobbed Daniel Platt from 18 yards to put Barwell one up. 
Despite Halesowen going close twice, Barwell made it two on 27 minutes when Ant Carney volleyed home from the edge of the box. 
Carney saw a shot hit the post before he made it three on 37 minutes after being set up by Brady Hickey. 
And he made it a first half hat-trick just before the break when he cut in from the left and rounded Platt before scoring. What do you think? Be the first to comment 
An unmarked Liam Kay headed home on 50 and Christie notched his second three minutes later after out muscling Aaron Griffiths. 
On 85 minutes, Julien was sent off for Barwell after being given his second yellow card for a trip but it was the home side who were celebrating. Receive daily email updates from the Express & Star
